{
  "stem": "9943.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] well, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I knew-- I did not mention that at all, but I knew languages.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in addition to studying Hebrew, as I did very solidly in the beginning of my life till, till the age of 11, in, in Rostov-on-the-Don, we had in the gymnasium, German and French.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Depending which school, and one-- and sometimes, it was both of these languages.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in Volodymyr-Volynskyi, we had English as a foreign, foreign language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And plus I was interested in languages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I used to read books from-- with the-- with a dictionary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so, so that was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And while I was in Warsaw, I continued to study English.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the third year of medicine-- or maybe that was the end of the third year of medicine, one of my [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] partners in the medical school, she knew German.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I knew Russian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I knew Russian and Polish and French and German and English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we started to translate-- summarize medical literature from foreign languages into Polish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So instead of lessons, as a way of making a living, we did-- and I-- she did translate from the German language because that's the language she knew, this partner of mine.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In medical school, you do certain things, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So she was my partner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was from-- from Lodz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I got to know her friends from Lodz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we became very friendly with each other-- so in this way, helping each other, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I, I, I was translating from American literature, the German Medical and American Medical Association from from London, from from Paris, and Russian literature into, into Polish.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it done-- it done two things for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
